  "faculty": "Chairperson Richard Wiebe Professor Associate Professor Assistant Professors Coordinator Patricia Arend Min Li Patricia Arend Zachary Miner",
  "description": [
    "The Sociology major is designed to provide students with refined approaches and methods of research and a broad understanding of the social world.",
    "The curriculum has been developed to provide the theoretical background and research skills essential for work concerned with human behavior. Graduates of the program are prepared for immediate entry into a wide variety of occupations in business, education, industry, social service, and public service settings. In addition, many graduates continue formal study by enrolling in advanced degree programs in sociology and related fields.",
    "The major requires 42 semester hours of course work. This total includes 12 semester hours of core Sociology courses, 12 semester hours of coursework from content clusters, 15 semester hours of Sociology electives, and 3 semester hours of Applied Statistics. Majors are encouraged to take advantage of relevant courses from the other majors in the Behavioral Sciences Department. Bachelor of Art students are required to have foreign language proficiency at the intermediate level."
  ],
